data.text:
November 2, 2021

Columbus, OH — Today, Ohio Democratic Party Chair Elizabeth Walters congratulated Toledo Mayor Wade Kapszukiewicz on his reelection as he continues to deliver for northwest Ohio, move Toledo forward and put working families first.

“Tonight was a well-earned victory not only for Mayor Kapszukiewicz and his team but also for all working families. The mayor has always put working families first, and under his leadership, Toledoans have already seen more jobs and meaningful investments in city infrastructure, housing and public safety. We look forward to even more results for working families in Toledo and around Ohio under his continued leadership,” said Chair Walters.
